# SC DataPack Pipeline — Optional Configuration
# ===============================================
# You do NOT need this file for the default setup.
# If Data.p4k is in the repo root folder, just run: python runner.py
#
# Only create a .env if you need to override the default paths
# (e.g. Data.p4k is on a different drive, or you want output elsewhere).
# Copy this file to .env and uncomment/edit the lines you need.

# Path to your Star Citizen Data.p4k
# Default: <repo root>\Data.p4k
# SC_P4K_PATH=C:\Games\StarCitizen\LIVE\Data.p4k

# Where to extract game files — created automatically on first run
# Default: <repo root>\Data_Extraction\
# SC_OUTPUT_DIR=C:\SC_output

# Where to save generated HTML reports — created automatically on first run
# Default: <repo root>\HTML\
# SC_REPORTS_DIR=C:\SC_reports
